latestPosts.caption:
Sheroes Hangout Cafe, Lucknow - Where Every Sip Tells a Story of Strength

Step into Sheroes Hangout Cafe in Lucknow, a space powered by acid attack survivors who are turning pain into purpose, one cup at a time.

Run by our fearless Sheroes, this cafe is more than just a place for food and coffee. It is a space of hope, healing, and powerful conversations.

Located in the heart of Lucknow, it welcomes locals, students, travelers, and supporters to come together, listen to stories of resilience, and stand with our brave women.

Every visit contributes to empowering our Sheroes and spreading awareness against acid violence.

Come for the coffee, stay for the strength. Visit us in Lucknow and be part of the movement.

Drop a comment to show your support
.
.
.

Chhanv Foundation is hiring for the role of State Coordinator and Trainer based in Pune. The selected candidate will be responsible for leading survivor outreach across Maharashtra, providing emotional and legal support, and conducting training sessions focused on skill development and rehabilitation.

If you have experience in social work, field coordination, or training, and want to be a part of a mission that transforms lives, send your CV and cover letter to 8826185246 or hr@chhanv.org.

To know more, visit www.chhanv.org

latestPosts.caption:
She was just a school-going girl from Jharkhand, returning home after tuition like every evening.

But someone had been watching her, following her, waiting for a moment to strike.

One day, he stopped her cycle and tried to force himself on her. Kajal ran and told her parents. She resisted him. 
And for that, he threw acid on her.

He tried to take away her face, her identity, her voice.

In seconds, her world turned into pain, silence, and scars that may never heal.

Kajal spent months in hospitals, wrapped in pain no child should ever feel. But she didn’t give up. She is still healing, still standing, still dreaming.

Her attacker is in jail, but justice hasn’t been delivered. The wait continues.

And Kajal? She now dreams of becoming an IAS officer, to protect those who cannot protect themselves.

She was attacked for saying no.
And today, she says yes to life, to hope, to a future she will rebuild herself.

Drop a 🌸 in the comments to let Kajal know her fight is not hers alone.

#stopacidattacks #justiceforkajal #acidattacksurvivors #supportsurvivors #shedeservesbetter #herstorymatters #frompaintopower #unbreakablespirit #endgenderviolence #chhanvfoundation

latestPosts.caption:
A heartbreaking betrayal shatters a life... 💔 

In Madhya Pradesh, a 21-year-old girl faced a brutal acid attack, simply fueled by a 'friend's' jealousy over her success. Imagine the unimaginable pain and trauma she's enduring. A young woman with bright dreams, now grappling with the aftermath of this heinous act.

This isn't just an isolated incident; it's a shocking crime against women and a deep stain on humanity. How can such betrayal and envy lead to an act designed to destroy a life? We must condemn this violence against women unequivocally.

Let's all come together to stand in solidarity with acid attack survivors. It is our collective responsibility to demand justice for her and for every survivor, and to bolster their spirits with unwavering support.

If you ever witness any form of gender-based violence or injustice around you, please speak up and do not stay silent. Your voice matters.

Drop a ❤️ in the comments to show your unwavering support for justice and resilience!

#stopacidattacks #chhanvfoundation #acidattacksurvivor #endacidviolence #justiceforher #crimeagainstwomen #madhyapradesh #speakup #resilience #nomoresilence

But behind every comeback is someone who held their hand through the darkest hours.

Your strength gives them courage.
Your support gives them willpower.
Your belief helps them reclaim their world.

💙 Thank you for standing with our Sheroes - not just as doctors, but as silent warriors of hope.
